HTML syntax

this is how a basic HTML file is set:

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>

	<title>name of title</title>
</head>


<body>

	<p>some text</p>
	<p>some text</p>
	<p>some text</p>
</body>

</html>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

<p>: basic paragraph

<h1>: large heading

<h2>: medium heading

<h3>: small heading

<br>: adds break

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Images

<img src="image.jpg" alt="whatever label you want to give it">

You can also denote the width and height of the image by doing:

<img src="image.jpg" width="pixels" height="pixels">
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

Links on Webpage

<a href ="https://site." target="_blank">Description of link</a>

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
